In England, in the seven days to 23 September, there were 183,613 new confirmed cases (324.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 16 September, there were 144,838 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 27% (38,775 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 28 September is 6,590,514 (11,654.3 cases per 100,000 population).
